<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="373" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1086,2013]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1230,1256]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Park &amp; Karisch, 2021" authorityName="Park &amp; Karisch" authorityYear="2021" box="[687,1117,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Dragmatucha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulcaniella">
<emphasis box="[687,849,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">D. vulcaniella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Park, K. - T. &amp; Karisch, T." box="[860,1117,1231,1257]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373" pagination="581 - 593" refId="ref10153" refString="Park, K. - T. &amp; Karisch, T. (2021) Lecithoceridae (Lepidoptera, Gelechioidea) of Bioko Island, with description of two new species (Lepidoptera, Gelechioidea, Lecithoceridae). Zootaxa, 4995 (3), 581 - 593. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4995.3.12" type="journal article" year="2021">Park &amp; Karisch, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which was described from Bioko, by having the forewing with orange ground color. These two species are only known species with orange ground color of the forewing. It can be distinguished from the latter by the forewing pattern lacking yellowish white antemedian and postmedian bands, and the hind wing with grayish shade broadly occupied. The female genitalia can easily be distinguished by having an extremely broad ductus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="373" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1086,2013]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1410,1436]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Description.</emphasis>
Female (
<figureCitation box="[453,603,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1603,1627]" captionTargetBox="[165,1411,216,1580]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1437,181,1580]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dragmatucha flavoaurea Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Adult, holotype; A1, Label; A2, Labial palpus; B, Female genitalia, GU-3886/Karisch, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810534" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810534/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Figs. 12A, A</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[604,619,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1836,1860]" captionTargetBox="[153,1434,600,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-247@2.[151,1436,597,1813]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. A: View from Mt. Tonkoui over the anthropogenic influenced tropical rain forest on the slopes (by T. Karisch, 25 viii 1997); B: Collecting site for light trapping with altimontane rain forest fragments at the South-Eastern slopes of Mt. Tonkoui (by T. Karisch, 25 viii 1997; C: Fragmentary secondary rain forest south of Gouédié (by T. Karisch, 20 viii 1997); D: Collecting site at the Southern border of Gouédié (by T. Karisch, 17 viii 1997)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810510/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">2</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 14.0 mm. 
<emphasis box="[877,938,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Head</emphasis>
: Pale orange dorsally; frons yellowish. Antenna slightly longer than forewing; scape elongated, pale orange; flagellum pale orange, paler beyond 2/3, without distinct annulations, slightly serrate, finely ciliate. Second palpomere of labial palpus long, slightly thickened, arched, pale orange on outer surface; 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[588,602,1518,1532]" fontSize="6" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">rd</superScript>
palpomere slender, strongly upturned, about 2/3 the length 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1287,1303,1518,1532]" fontSize="6" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">nd</superScript>
palpomere. 
<emphasis box="[151,232,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pale orange, tegula same color. Hind tibia pale orange, with a short, blackish scale-tuft medially and at distal end; spurs pale yellowish. Forewing ground color pale orange; antemedian fascia broad pale grayish brown; postmedian fascia broadly suffused with pale brownish scales; a small dark-brown dot near middle of cell; costa arched in basal 1/3; apex slightly produced; termen oblique; fringe pale orange. Hind wing yellowish orange, with grayish shade broadly occupied in the middle; apex produced; fringe yellowish orange.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1086,2013]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis box="[199,390,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[405,507,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1603,1627]" captionTargetBox="[165,1411,216,1580]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1437,181,1580]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dragmatucha flavoaurea Park &amp; Karisch, sp. nov.: A, Adult, holotype; A1, Label; A2, Labial palpus; B, Female genitalia, GU-3886/Karisch, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810534" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810534/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
): Abdominal sternite VIII slightly emarginated medially. Apophyses anteriores less than 1/2 the length of apophyses posteriores. Ostium bursae concave. Antrum bowl-shaped, sclerotized, short. Ductus bursae extremely broad, necked between antrum and ductus bursae, without conjunction with corpus bursae. Signum in corpus bursae rather small, upper and lower plates asymmetrical, upper one larger.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1086,2013]" box="[199,376,1879,1905]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Male unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
