<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="373" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1086,2013]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1951,1977]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin, - 
<emphasis box="[862,929,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">flavus</emphasis>
(= yellow) and - 
<emphasis box="[1124,1199,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">aureus</emphasis>
(= golden), referring to the yellowish ground color of the forewing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
